Hereto if wee add Saint Hieromes note upon the text in Malachy, the name Sunday may bee improved to a more profitable uſe, thus;
Orietur Sol Juſtitiae, quiverè omnia indicabit, & nec bona nec mala, nec virtutes nec vitia latere patietur. Hier. in Mal. 4.2. tom. 6. pag. 365. col. 2. 
                  The Lord, as the Sun, will bring every thing to light, ſo that (as he ſaith) he will ſuffer neither good nor bad, vertue nor vice any more to lye hid.

